text_lines.text: Services Agreement
This Services Agreement (the "Agreement") is entered into as of July 1, 2020 (the
"Effective Date") by and between Island Physical Therapy and Chiropractic PLLC("Customer"),
organized under the Laws of the State of NY, whose present address is 740 Veteran's Memorial
Highway Suite 210, Hauppauge, NY, 11788and Comprehensive Business Development, LLC,
("Company"), organized under the Laws of the State of New Jersey ("Company"), whose present
address is 16 Mitchell Court, Marlboro, New Jersey 07746.
WHEREAS, Customer desires to procure the Services (as defined in Section 1 below) on
the terms and conditions set forth herein.
NOW, THEREFORE, for the mutual promises, representations, warranties and covenants
contained herein, the parties agree as follows:
Company Services. Subject to the terms and conditions of this Agreement and the
payment of the fees set forth in Section 4(a) below, Company shall provide certain marketing
services on behalf of Customer as set forth on Exhibit A (the "Services"). If there is any conflict
between the provisions of this Agreement and Exhibit A with respect to the Services to be
performed by Company, the provisions of Exhibit A shall control. For purposes of this
Agreement, "Customer Members" shall mean healthcare providers and other staff employed or
engaged by Customer. Company grants Customer and its Customer Members the right to access
and use the Services, including various websites (the "Company Sites"), as applicable. Customer
shall be responsible for any use of the Services, and/or Company Sites by such Customer Members.
Customer Responsibilities.
Customer will furnish to Company such cooperation, technical assistance,
resources and support, as reasonably necessary or appropriate for Company to implement and
perform the Services, as applicable.
Customer recognizes and confirms that in providing the Services under this
b.
Agreement, the Company will be using and relying upon data, material and other information
("Information")
furnished
by the Customer's management,
employees
representatives. Customer will cooperate with Company to verify the Information to be utilized
by Company in rendering the Services, including information to be displayed on the Company
Sites, as applicable. Customer hereby agrees and represents that all Information furnished in
connection with this engagement, to the best extent of its knowledge, shall be accurate and
complete in all material respects at the time furnished unless Company is otherwise notified by the
Customer, and Customer further agrees that it will promptly notify Company of any subsequent
material change affecting the accuracy or completeness of such Information. Customer recognizes
and agrees that Company assumes no responsibility for the accuracy and completeness of such
Information and that Customer is solely responsible for any liability or expense resulting from
outdated or inaccurate Customer Information. Customer further guarantees any elements of text,
graphics, photos, designs, trademarks, or other artwork provided to Company for inclusion on the
Comprehensive Business Development, LLC.
